{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Message sent to team-lead's inbox",
  "routing": {
    "sender": "steve-schoger",
    "senderColor": "cyan",
    "target": "@team-lead",
    "targetColor": "red",
    "summary": "CONSENT on all 13 retro changes, notes on 3 items",
    "content": "**CONSENT -- all 13 changes.**\n\nQuick notes on a few items from a design perspective:\n\n**#5 (Accessible Names Checklist):** Strong support. \"Delete: Buy groceries\" is better UX too, not just better a11y. It gives context when scanning a list of actions. This is a visual hierarchy win as well.\n\n**#10 (Deferred Items Tracking):** This directly addresses my concern about losing non-blocking design notes. I would like the file to be `docs/deferred-items.md` (not just design -- it should capture a11y, UX, and CSS deviations too, as proposed). I have 9 items ready to populate it from Tasks #11 and #15 once Luca creates the file.\n\n**#3 (Refactor Step):** Agreed -- the refactor step applies to CSS too. After getting a component working, tighten up the token usage, consolidate duplicate declarations, and check spacing consistency before committing.\n\nNo objections on any of the 13. Ship it."
  }
}
